title: Grateful Dead Live at San Francisco Civic Auditorium on 1983-12-30
description: Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Ramble On Rose, Little Red Rooster, Brown Eyed Women-> Looks Like Rain-> Deal Shakedown Street, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Heaven Help The Fool Jam-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: Day Job

reviews.review_text: Good sound, decent show Clean sound, and the playing is smooth, even if the overall impression is kind of low energy (streaming it at work, so I may have missed some fireworks along the way). Keyboards are pretty clear and everybody sounds like they were on that night. Should make for good late-night listening sometime.

Come West My Freiend Well this night was hot  a great Berta too start off the show and me and Tommy were in the front again The second set was Going off to with a great Shakedown Terripin Mind and Body Jam And Truckin for Tommy Coming to Calil too see The Dead on The New year run The Band was Jamin and so were we  Light em up Jerry.

night before new years I always loved the night before New Years Eve then New years Eve itself.  The boys always seemed a little more relaxed.  This was a great show as I can recall.  I had to trade my New Years tix for a ticket to this show. I got a another New Years tix. right after the show. "Goes to show you don't always know".  I went to alot of shows and I don't think there was a show I didn't like.  So I always give five stars to shows I was at.

solid performance First set doesn't have all that much worth noting other than FOTD, but that song is almost always great with Brent. 

Same goes for the second set... at least pre-drums. Jerry pulls out some awesome (abeit sloppy) leads on Terrapin, but pretty much everything else is good but not mind-blowing. This changes, however, when the band starts going into the (in)famous Mind Left Body Jam out of space. The Truckin, Wharf Rat, and Good Lovin' that follow are all very well-played... and the Day Job at least has enough momentum behind it to not be all that annoying. Overall, this is a good show, but nothing completely amazing or mandatory.
watching this Am watching this show on you tube this early morning. The end of one my favorite years on tour, Happy New Years people
